50|$|PncA is a gene {{encoding}} pyrazinamidase in Mycobacterium species. Pyrazinamidase converts {{the drug}} <b>pyrazinamide</b> to the active form pyrazinoic acid. There is {{a strong correlation between}} mutations in pncA and resistance of M. tuberculosis to <b>pyrazinamide.</b>|$|E
